T-series burstable instances.

The t-three and t-four-g families don't give you full see-pee-you all the time. Instead they run at a baseline percentage and earn credits while they sit below that baseline. When you burst above it, you spend those credits.

There are two modes for when the credits run out. In standard mode, the see-pee-you is simply capped back at the baseline. In unlimited mode, which is the default, the instance keeps bursting but you pay extra for the overage.

Use t-series for workloads with idle stretches and occasional spikes, like low-traffic web servers, dev boxes, and internal tools. Don't use them for sustained, see-pee-you-heavy work, because you'll either get throttled or quietly rack up unlimited-mode charges.
